00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:50,520
Seminary was founded in 1924, bankruptcy knocked at the doors. And by noon on one particular day,

536
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:56,800
every creditor threatened to foreclose the school. And that morning, the founders of the seminary

537
00:35:56,800 --> 00:36:01,580
met to pray in President Louis Sperry Schaeffer's office, and they asked God to provide the needed

538
00:36:01,580 --> 00:36:08,210
funds. And Harry Ironside was part of that prayer meeting. And when it was his turn to pray,

539
00:36:09,090 --> 00:36:12,850
he prayed in his very characteristically pointed manner. He prayed this,

540
00:36:13,450 --> 00:36:21,400
Lord, we know the cattle on a thousand hills are thine. Please sell some of them and send us

541
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:29,840
the money. Now that's faith. That is pointed prayer. Meanwhile, as his men were praying,

542
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:36,580
Into the seminary's business office came a tall Texan, and addressing the secretary, he said this,

543
00:36:36,580 --> 00:36:41,360
I just sold two carloads of cattle in Fort Worth. I've been trying to make another business deal go

544
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:46,320
through, and it won't work. I feel that God is compelling me to give some money of this cattle

545
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:52,900
money to the seminary. I don't know if you need it or not, but here's the check. Well, the secretary

546
00:36:52,900 --> 00:36:58,400
was well aware of what the prayer meeting was about in the next room. She also knew how serious

547
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:00,340
the financial straits the seminary was in.

548
00:37:01,610 --> 00:37:04,050
And so she took the check and knocked on the door,

549
00:37:04,570 --> 00:37:08,560
and they finally got a response, and they welcomed her in,

550
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:11,220
and she presented the check to Louis Sperry Schaefer,

551
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:14,480
and he stood and looked at it with amazement

552
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:19,080
because the amount of the check exactly was the amount of the debt

553
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:20,520
that was needed to be paid.

554
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:22,120
Exactly.

555
00:37:24,840 --> 00:37:26,500
And looking at the signature on the check,

556
00:37:27,770 --> 00:37:29,890
this gentleman recognized the name of the cattle rancher.

557
00:37:30,860 --> 00:37:33,420
And he turned to Harry Ironside, the one who had prayed so boldly,

